items.title: Heaney (shoulder) to miss at least one start
items.summary: Angels left-hander Andrew Heaney will not make his next scheduled start against the Rangers on Friday due to a shoulder impingement, manager Mike Scioscia said Tuesday.

items.title: Freeland avoids injury after comebacker
items.summary: Rockies left-handed pitcher Kyle Freeland checked out fine Tuesday after being hit on his throwing shoulder and jaw by a J.D. Martinez line drive during Monday night's 5-4 victory over the D-backs.

items.title: Sherfy turning in big innings for D-backs
items.summary: In the winter of 2016, fresh off his first season with the Triple-A Reno Aces, Jimmie Sherfy found himself in a situation familiar to many Minor League players who are chasing their Major League dreams. It was time to get an offseason job to make ends meet.

items.title: 2007 NL champs reuniting at Coors on Friday
items.summary: While the current Rockies club tries to make its playoff mark, the squad that 10 years ago brought the greatest moments in team history is planning a rousing reunion at Coors Field.
